sentences: Jerry Fuller (born November 19, 1938) is an American songwriter, singer and record producer.
In 1959, he moved to Los Angeles, California, and secured a performing contract with Challenge Records.
In 1961, he wrote "Travelin' Man" which was originally intended for Sam Cooke.
On his return in 1963, Challenge / Four Star moved him to New York City to run its east coast operation.
There he discovered a garage band, The Knickerbockers, and produced their 1965 hit "Lies".
In 1967, he moved to Columbia Records as a producer.
In 1970 he started Moonchild production company, writing and producing the hit "Show and Tell" for Al Wilson in 1973.
